						               													<description>A holiday twist on the classic detective game! In Clue: North Pole Edition, instead of solving a murder mystery, players attempt to solve the mystery of the missing presents.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players move from building to building at the North Pole to solve the mystery of: who did it, with what, and where? Players are dealt character, item, and location cards after the top card from each card type is secretly placed in the Sleigh Room in the middle of the board. Players must move to a location and then make an accusation against a character saying they did it in that room with a specific item. The player to the left must show one of any cards accused to the accuser if in that player's hand. Through deductive reasoning each player must figure out which character, item, and location are in the secret file. To do this, each player must uncover what cards are in other players hands by making more and more accusations. Once a player knows what cards the other players are holding, they will know what cards are in the hidden in the Sleigh Room.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
